==English==

===Etymology===
From the [[Greek]] verb ''[[ευχαριστώ]]'' (efkharistó), meaning “to gratify”, “to rejoice” and “to thank”

===Noun===
<!-- proper noun? -->
'''Eucharist'''

# The sacrament of the Eucharist. One of the 7 sacraments of the Catholic Church.
# The body and blood of Christ, believed to be substantially present under the appearances of the bread and wine offered at Mass.
# The liturgy of the ~. This meaning refers to the main, sacrificial part of the [[Latin rite]] [[Mass]] in particular.
# Celebration of the ~. This refers to the entire Mass (or Eastern [[Divine Liturgy]]) in general. 

